{"title_page": "Efrem Hill", "text_new": "{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name          = Efrem Hill\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| number        = 5, 15, 80\n| position      = [[Wide receiver]]\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1983|7|23}}\n| birth_place   = [[Birmingham, Alabama]]\n| height_ft     = 6\n| height_in     = 0\n| weight_lbs    = 188\n| college       = [[Samford Bulldogs football|Samford]]\n| high_school   = [[North Springs Charter School of Arts and Sciences|North Springs]]\n| undraftedyear = 2005\n| pastteams     = \n* [[Carolina Panthers]] ({{NFL Year|2005}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2006}})*\n* [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] ({{NFL Year|2007}})*\n* [[Cleveland Browns]] ({{NFL Year|2007}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2008}})*\n* [[Edmonton Eskimos]] ({{CFL Year|2009}}\u2013{{CFL Year|2010}})\n* [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] ({{CFL Year|2011}}\u2013{{CFL Year|2012}})\n* [[Georgia Fire]] (2014)*\n| cflstatus     = International\n| highlights    = \n* 2003 [[Ohio Valley Conference|OVC]] Male Athlete of the Year\n* 2003 Consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]]\n* 2003 OVC Offensive Player of the Year\n* 2003 [[Walter Payton Award]] Finalist\n* 2002 [[Football Championship Subdivision|I-AA]] All-Independent First-Team Offense\n| nfl           = HIL208693\n| cfl           = 2477\n| cflstatlabel1 = [[Reception (gridiron football)|Receptions]]\n| cflstatvalue1 = 100\n| cflstatlabel2 = Receiving yards\n| cflstatvalue2 = 1,184\n| cflstatlabel3 = Receiving [[touchdown]]s\n| cflstatvalue3 = 2\n}}\n'''Efrem Dale Hill''' (born July 23, 1983) if a former professional [[gridiron football]] [[wide receiver]]. He was signed as an [[undrafted free agent]] by the [[Carolina Panthers]] in 2005. He played [[college football]] for the [[Samford University|Samford Bulldogs]]. Hill was also a member of the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]], [[Cleveland Browns]], [[Edmonton Eskimos]], [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] and [[Georgia Fire]].\n\n==Early years==\nHill attended [[North Springs High School]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. During his [[Twelfth grade|senior]] season, he had 680 yards passing and 943 yards rushing. Hill started at quarterback from his [[Tenth grade|sophomore]]-senior seasons, earning the team's Best Back Award for two consecutive seasons and the Coach's Corner Award. Hill was a three-sport athlete at North Springs, also playing [[baseball]] and [[basketball]]. He was a member of North Fulton's Super 11, he helped lead North Springs to the quarterfinal round and an eighth-place finish in the state. He placed ninth in the state in the triple jump with a height of 43' 13\".\n\n==College career==\nWhile at Samford, Hill majored in [[Business]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html |title=Player Bio:Efrem Hill |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708212118/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html |archivedate=2011-07-08 }}</ref>\n\n=== Freshman (2001)===\nIn 2001, Hill finished second on the team in receiving with 12 [[Reception (American football)|reception]]s for 114 yards. He had one reception in his first three games, catching one for 11 yards against [[University of Tennessee at Chattanooga#Athletics|Chattanooga]], one for 10 yards against [[Nicholls State University#Athletics|Nicholls State]] and one for a season-long 24 yards against [[Jacksonville State University#Athletics|Jacksonville State]]. He had two receptions in each of the next three games. He had two receptions for 12 yards against [[Charleston Southern University#Athletics|Charleston Southern]]. He had two catches for seven yards against [[University of Tennessee at Martin#Athletics|UT-Martin]]. Hill caught two passes for 23 yards against [[Elon University#Athletics|Elon]]. He set a career-high with three catches for 27 yards against [[Virginia Military Institute#Football|VMI]] in the season finale.\n\n===Sophomore (2002)===\nIn 2002, Hill finished second on the team in receiving for the second consecutive season with 569 yards on 39 receptions and six [[touchdown]]s. He also returned three kickoffs for 102 yards. Hill finished the season with back-to-back 100-yard receiving games. He caught five passes for 102 yards and one touchdown at [[Southeast Missouri State College#Athletic team names and mascot|Southeast Missouri State]]. Hill caught a season- and career-high six receptions for 125 yards and two touchdowns at [[Youngstown State Penguins#Football|Youngstown State]]. He was named I-AA Independent Offensive Player of the Week after his performance at Youngstown State.\n\n===Junior (2003)===\nIn 2003, Hill was a consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-America]] selection.<ref name=\"Bio Bill Gray\">{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gray_bill00.html |title=Bio Bill Gray |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080406204441/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gray_bill00.html |archivedate=2008-04-06 }}</ref> He was also, a [[Walter Payton Award]] finalist.<ref name=\"Bio Bill Gray\"/> He was named [[Ohio Valley Conference]] Offensive Player of the Year and Male Athlete of the Year.\n\nFor the season he had 92 receptions for a school-record 1,387 yards. He led the nation in yards per game, averaging 126.09. Hill led the conference in: receiving yards per game, receptions per game (8.36), scoring (8.2 ppg.) and scoring by touchdown (8.2 ppg.).\n\nHill caught seven passes for 107 yards and a touchdown at Chattanooga. He caught nine passes for 148 yards and a season-high three touchdowns against [[University of West Alabama#Men's Sports|West Alabama]]. He recorded eight receptions for 87 yards at [[San Diego State University|San Diego State]]. He caught four passes for 104 yards and a 64-yard touchdown at [[Eastern Kentucky University#Athletics|Eastern Kentucky]]. Hill caught 11 passes for a career-high 223 yards at UT-Martin. He caught eight passes for 95 yards and two touchdowns against [[Tennessee State University|Tennessee State]]. He caught 10 passes for 112 yards at [[Tennessee Technological University#Men's|Tennessee Tech]]. Hill had a school-record 16 receptions for 197 yards and two touchdowns against Jacksonville State. He caught 10 passes for 151 yards and a touchdown at [[Eastern Illinois Panthers|Eastern Illinois]].\n\n===Senior (2004)===\nIn 2004, Hill played in all 11 games leading the team in all receiving categories. He was also second on the team in punt returns with six for 50 yards with an average of 8.3 yards per return.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/teamcume.html |title=Overall Individual Statistics |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Hill recorded nine receptions for 209 yards (long of being 84 yards) and three touchdowns, against West Alabama. He also returned one punt for four yards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game1.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats UWA vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football|Georgia Tech]] Hill had 11 receptions for 83 yards (long of 26 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game2.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Samford vs. Georgia Tech |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Furman University#Athletics|Furman]], Hill had 10 receptions for 88 yards (long of 15 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game3.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Furman vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> In the game against Southeast Missouri, Hill had seven receptions for 84 yards (long of 15 yards). He also returned two punts for 29 yards (long of 24 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game4.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Southeast Missouri vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> At Eastern Kentucky, Hill had six receptions for 84 yards (long of 39 yards) and three touchdowns.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game5.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Eastern Kentucky vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Murray State University#Athletics|Murray State]], Hill had six catches for 95 yards (long of 34 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game6.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Murray State vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against UT-Martin, Hill had two receptions for 25 yards (long of 13 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game7.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats UT-Martin vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> At Tennessee State, Hill had seven catches for 99 yards (long of 31 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game8.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Samford vs. Tennessee State |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against Tennessee Tech, Hill had six receptions for 163 yards (long of 74 yards) and one touchdown. He also had one punt return for one yard.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game9.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Tennessee Tech vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against Jacksonville State, Hill had four catches for 28 yards (long of 14 yards). He also returned two punts for 16 yards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game10.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Jacksonville State vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> In the season finale against Eastern Illinois, Hill had three catches for 28 yards (long of 19 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game11.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Eastern Illinois vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref>\n\nThen in 2005, after the 2004 bowl season was over, Hill played in [[Gridiron Classic (1999\u20132005)|The Villages Gridiron Classic]] College All-Star Game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/010605aaa.html |title=Efrem Hill To Play In The Villages Gridiron Classic |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref>\n\n===Career statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=0 style=\"background: #FFFFFF;\"\n|colspan=3 align=\"center\"|Career Statistics ||colspan=5 align=\"center\"| Receiving\n|-\n| '''Year''' || '''Team''' || '''G''' ||  '''Rec''' || '''Yards''' || '''Y/R''' || '''TD''' || '''LNG'''\n|-\n| 2001 || Samford Bulldogs || 7<ref>http://www.foxsports.com/college-football/efrem-hill-player-stats</ref> || 12 || 114 || 9.5 || 0 || --\n|-\n| 2002 || Samford Bulldogs |11|| 39 || 569 || 14.6 || 6 || --\n|-\n| 2003 || Samford Bulldogs |11 || 92 || 1,387 || 15.0 || 15 || 81\n|-\n| 2004 || Samford Bulldogs || 11 || 71 || 984 || 13.9 || 10 || 84\n|-\n| Total ||  || 40 || 214 || 3,054 || 14.3 || 31 || 84\n|}\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Carolina Panthers===\nIn 2005, Hill went undrafted in the [[2005 NFL Draft]]. However, he was signed by the [[Carolina Panthers]] on April 29, 2005.<ref name=Hill>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 |title=Cleveland Browns - Players - Efrem Hill |accessdate=2007-07-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071017003319/http://clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 |archivedate=2007-10-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref> After being waived from the Panthers on September 3, 2005, he was signed to the Panthers [[practice squad]] two days later.<ref name=Hill/> He was then signed to the Panthers active roster on December 20, 2005.<ref name=Hill/> Hill was then waived by the Panthers on September 2, 2006,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.panthers.com/Common/Article.aspx?id=10512 |title=Panthers make final cuts |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=Panthers.com}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> he was then signed to the team's practice squad on October 17, 2006.<ref name=\"Hill\"/>\n\n===Tampa Bay Buccaneers===\nHill was signed by the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on January 17, 2007.<ref name=\"Hill\" /> He was later waived by the Buccaneers on June 25, 2007.<ref name=\"Hill\" />\n\n===Cleveland Browns===\nOn June 26, 2007, Hill was claimed off waivers by the [[Cleveland Browns]].<ref name=\"Hill\" />\n\n===Edmonton Eskimos===\nHill signed with the [[Edmonton Eskimos]] on May 20, 2009.\n\n===Saskatchewan Roughriders===\n\nOn April 20, 2011, it was announced that Hill had signed with the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]].<ref>https://www.cfl.ca/article/riders-add-receivers-hill-and-wheelwright {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921065557/http://www.cfl.ca/article/riders-add-receivers-hill-and-wheelwright |date=2012-09-21 }} Riders add receivers Hill and Wheelwright</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHill was married at age 22, and currently has a young daughter and son. He holds the head football coaching position at Discovery High School in Lawrenceville, Georgia. He is also the head coach for Discovery's track team.<ref>http://highschoolsports.blog.ajc.com/2016/03/22/discovery-hires-former-nfl-player-hill/</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071017003319/http://clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 Browns bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110708212118/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html College bio]\n* [http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/players/profile?playerId=9426 Player card] on [[ESPN.com]]\n* [http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/players/7571/ Profile] on [[SI.com]]\n* [http://www.sportsline.com/nfl/players/playerpage/551378 Profile] on [[CBS Sports.com]]\n* [https://sports.yahoo.com/nfl/players/7571 Profile] on [[Yahoo! Sports]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110930105923/http://www.nfldraftscout.com/ratings/profile.php?pyid=54085 Draft profile] on NFLDraftScout.com\n* [http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/2005/draft/players/56212.html Draft profile] on SI.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hill, Efrem}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Atlanta]]\n[[Category:American football wide receivers]]\n[[Category:Canadian football wide receivers]]\n[[Category:American players of Canadian football]]\n[[Category:Samford Bulldogs football players]]\n[[Category:Carolina Panthers players]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers players]]\n[[Category:Cleveland Browns players]]\n[[Category:Edmonton Eskimos players]]\n[[Category:Saskatchewan Roughriders players]]\n[[Category:Georgia Fire players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name          = Efrem Hill\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| number        = 5, 15, 80\n| position      = [[Wide receiver]]\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1983|7|23}}\n| birth_place   = [[Birmingham, Alabama]]\n| height_ft     = 6\n| height_in     = 0\n| weight_lbs    = 188\n| college       = [[Samford Bulldogs football|Samford]]\n| high_school   = [[North Springs Charter School of Arts and Sciences|North Springs]]\n| undraftedyear = 2005\n| pastteams     = \n* [[Carolina Panthers]] ({{NFL Year|2005}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2006}})*\n* [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] ({{NFL Year|2007}})*\n* [[Cleveland Browns]] ({{NFL Year|2007}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2008}})*\n* [[Edmonton Eskimos]] ({{CFL Year|2009}}\u2013{{CFL Year|2010}})\n* [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] ({{CFL Year|2011}}\u2013{{CFL Year|2012}})\n* [[Georgia Fire]] (2014)*\n| cflstatus     = International\n| highlights    = \n* 2003 [[Ohio Valley Conference|OVC]] Male Athlete of the Year\n* 2003 Consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]]\n* 2003 OVC Offensive Player of the Year\n* 2003 [[Walter Payton Award]] Finalist\n* 2002 [[Football Championship Subdivision|I-AA]] All-Independent First-Team Offense\n| nfl           = HIL208693\n| cfl           = 2477\n| cflstatlabel1 = [[Reception (gridiron football)|Receptions]]\n| cflstatvalue1 = 100\n| cflstatlabel2 = Receiving yards\n| cflstatvalue2 = 1,184\n| cflstatlabel3 = Receiving [[touchdown]]s\n| cflstatvalue3 = 2\n}}\n'''Efrem Dale Hill''' (born July 23, 1983) if a former professional [[gridiron football]] [[wide receiver]]. He was signed as an [[undrafted free agent]] by the [[Carolina Panthers]] in 2005. He played [[college football]] for the [[Samford University|Samford Bulldogs]]. Hill was also a member of the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]], [[Cleveland Browns]], [[Edmonton Eskimos]], [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] and [[Georgia Fire]].\n\n==Early years==\nHill attended [[North Springs High School]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. During his [[Twelfth grade|senior]] season, he had 680 yards passing and 943 yards rushing. Hill started at quarterback from his [[Tenth grade|sophomore]]-senior seasons, earning the team's Best Back Award for two consecutive seasons and the Coach's Corner Award. Hill was a three-sport athlete at North Springs, also playing [[baseball]] and [[basketball]]. He was a member of North Fulton's Super 11, he helped lead North Springs to the quarterfinal round and an eighth-place finish in the state. He placed ninth in the state in the triple jump with a height of 43' 13\".\n\n==College career==\nWhile at Samford, Hill majored in [[Business]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html |title=Player Bio:Efrem Hill |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708212118/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html |archivedate=2011-07-08 }}</ref>\n\n=== Freshman (2001)===\nIn 2001, Hill finished second on the team in receiving with 12 [[Reception (American football)|reception]]s for 114 yards. He had one reception in his first three games, catching one for 11 yards against [[University of Tennessee at Chattanooga#Athletics|Chattanooga]], one for 10 yards against [[Nicholls State University#Athletics|Nicholls State]] and one for a season-long 24 yards against [[Jacksonville State University#Athletics|Jacksonville State]]. He had two receptions in each of the next three games. He had two receptions for 12 yards against [[Charleston Southern University#Athletics|Charleston Southern]]. He had two catches for seven yards against [[University of Tennessee at Martin#Athletics|UT-Martin]]. Hill caught two passes for 23 yards against [[Elon University#Athletics|Elon]]. He set a career-high with three catches for 27 yards against [[Virginia Military Institute#Football|VMI]] in the season finale.\n\n===Sophomore (2002)===\nIn 2002, Hill finished second on the team in receiving for the second consecutive season with 569 yards on 39 receptions and six [[touchdown]]s. He also returned three kickoffs for 102 yards. Hill finished the season with back-to-back 100-yard receiving games. He caught five passes for 102 yards and one touchdown at [[Southeast Missouri State College#Athletic team names and mascot|Southeast Missouri State]]. Hill caught a season- and career-high six receptions for 125 yards and two touchdowns at [[Youngstown State Penguins#Football|Youngstown State]]. He was named I-AA Independent Offensive Player of the Week after his performance at Youngstown State.\n\n===Junior (2003)===\nIn 2003, Hill was a consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-America]] selection.<ref name=\"Bio Bill Gray\">{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gray_bill00.html |title=Bio Bill Gray |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080406204441/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gray_bill00.html |archivedate=2008-04-06 }}</ref> He was also, a [[Walter Payton Award]] finalist.<ref name=\"Bio Bill Gray\"/> He was named [[Ohio Valley Conference]] Offensive Player of the Year and Male Athlete of the Year.\n\nFor the season he had 92 receptions for a school-record 1,387 yards. He led the nation in yards per game, averaging 126.09. Hill led the conference in: receiving yards per game, receptions per game (8.36), scoring (8.2 ppg.) and scoring by touchdown (8.2 ppg.).\n\nHill caught seven passes for 107 yards and a touchdown at Chattanooga. He caught nine passes for 148 yards and a season-high three touchdowns against [[University of West Alabama#Men's Sports|West Alabama]]. He recorded eight receptions for 87 yards at [[San Diego State University|San Diego State]]. He caught four passes for 104 yards and a 64-yard touchdown at [[Eastern Kentucky University#Athletics|Eastern Kentucky]]. Hill caught 11 passes for a career-high 223 yards at UT-Martin. He caught eight passes for 95 yards and two touchdowns against [[Tennessee State University|Tennessee State]]. He caught 10 passes for 112 yards at [[Tennessee Technological University#Men's|Tennessee Tech]]. Hill had a school-record 16 receptions for 197 yards and two touchdowns against Jacksonville State. He caught 10 passes for 151 yards and a touchdown at [[Eastern Illinois Panthers|Eastern Illinois]].\n\n===Senior (2004)===\nIn 2004, Hill played in all 11 games leading the team in all receiving categories. He was also second on the team in punt returns with six for 50 yards with an average of 8.3 yards per return.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/teamcume.html |title=Overall Individual Statistics |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Hill recorded nine receptions for 209 yards (long of being 84 yards) and three touchdowns, against West Alabama. He also returned one punt for four yards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game1.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats UWA vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football|Georgia Tech]] Hill had 11 receptions for 83 yards (long of 26 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game2.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Samford vs. Georgia Tech |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Furman University#Athletics|Furman]], Hill had 10 receptions for 88 yards (long of 15 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game3.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Furman vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> In the game against Southeast Missouri, Hill had seven receptions for 84 yards (long of 15 yards). He also returned two punts for 29 yards (long of 24 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game4.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Southeast Missouri vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> At Eastern Kentucky, Hill had six receptions for 84 yards (long of 39 yards) and three touchdowns.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game5.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Eastern Kentucky vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against [[Murray State University#Athletics|Murray State]], Hill had six catches for 95 yards (long of 34 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game6.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Murray State vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against UT-Martin, Hill had two receptions for 25 yards (long of 13 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game7.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats UT-Martin vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> At Tennessee State, Hill had seven catches for 99 yards (long of 31 yards) and one touchdown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game8.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Samford vs. Tennessee State |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against Tennessee Tech, Hill had six receptions for 163 yards (long of 74 yards) and one touchdown. He also had one punt return for one yard.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game9.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Tennessee Tech vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> Against Jacksonville State, Hill had four catches for 28 yards (long of 14 yards). He also returned two punts for 16 yards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game10.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Jacksonville State vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref> In the season finale against Eastern Illinois, Hill had three catches for 28 yards (long of 19 yards).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/stats/2004-2005/game11.html |title=2004-2005 Game stats Eastern Illinois vs. Samford |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref>\n\nThen in 2005, after the 2004 bowl season was over, Hill played in [[Gridiron Classic (1999\u20132005)|The Villages Gridiron Classic]] College All-Star Game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/010605aaa.html |title=Efrem Hill To Play In The Villages Gridiron Classic |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=SamfordSports.CSTV.com}}</ref>\n\n===Career statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=0 style=\"background: #FFFFFF;\"\n|colspan=3 align=\"center\"|Career Statistics ||colspan=5 align=\"center\"| Receiving\n|-\n| '''Year''' || '''Team''' || '''G''' ||  '''Rec''' || '''Yards''' || '''Y/R''' || '''TD''' || '''LNG'''\n|-\n| 2001 || Samford Bulldogs || 7<ref>http://www.foxsports.com/college-football/efrem-hill-player-stats</ref> || 12 || 114 || 9.5 || 0 || --\n|-\n| 2002 || Samford Bulldogs |11|| 39 || 569 || 14.6 || 6 || --\n|-\n| 2003 || Samford Bulldogs |11 || 92 || 1,387 || 15.0 || 15 || 81\n|-\n| 2004 || Samford Bulldogs || 11 || 71 || 984 || 13.9 || 10 || 84\n|-\n| Total ||  || 40 || 214 || 3,054 || 14.3 || 31 || 84\n|}\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Carolina Panthers===\nIn 2005, Hill went undrafted in the [[2005 NFL Draft]]. However, he was signed by the [[Carolina Panthers]] on April 29, 2005.<ref name=Hill>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 |title=Cleveland Browns - Players - Efrem Hill |accessdate=2007-07-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071017003319/http://clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 |archivedate=2007-10-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref> After being waived from the Panthers on September 3, 2005, he was signed to the Panthers [[practice squad]] two days later.<ref name=Hill/> He was then signed to the Panthers active roster on December 20, 2005.<ref name=Hill/> Hill was then waived by the Panthers on September 2, 2006,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.panthers.com/Common/Article.aspx?id=10512 |title=Panthers make final cuts |accessdate=2008-03-24 |work=Panthers.com}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> he was then signed to the teams practice squad on October 17, 2006.<ref name=\"Hill\"/>\n\n===Tampa Bay Buccaneers===\nHill was signed by the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on January 17, 2007.<ref name=\"Hill\" /> He was later waived by the Buccaneers on June 25, 2007.<ref name=\"Hill\" />\n\n===Cleveland Browns===\nOn June 26, 2007, Hill was claimed off waivers by the [[Cleveland Browns]].<ref name=\"Hill\" />\n\n===Edmonton Eskimos===\nHill signed with the [[Edmonton Eskimos]] on May 20, 2009.\n\n===Saskatchewan Roughriders===\n\nOn April 20, 2011, it was announced that Hill had signed with the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]].<ref>https://www.cfl.ca/article/riders-add-receivers-hill-and-wheelwright {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921065557/http://www.cfl.ca/article/riders-add-receivers-hill-and-wheelwright |date=2012-09-21 }} Riders add receivers Hill and Wheelwright</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHill was married at age 22, and currently has a young daughter and son. He holds the head football coaching position at Discovery High School in Lawrenceville, Georgia. He is also the head coach for Discovery's track team. <ref>http://highschoolsports.blog.ajc.com/2016/03/22/discovery-hires-former-nfl-player-hill/</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071017003319/http://clevelandbrowns.com/team/player.php?id=3159 Browns bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110708212118/http://samfordsports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/hill_efrem00.html College bio]\n* [http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/players/profile?playerId=9426 Player card] on [[ESPN.com]]\n* [http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/players/7571/ Profile] on [[SI.com]]\n* [http://www.sportsline.com/nfl/players/playerpage/551378 Profile] on [[CBS Sports.com]]\n* [https://sports.yahoo.com/nfl/players/7571 Profile] on [[Yahoo! Sports]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110930105923/http://www.nfldraftscout.com/ratings/profile.php?pyid=54085 Draft profile] on NFLDraftScout.com\n* [http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/2005/draft/players/56212.html Draft profile] on SI.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hill, Efrem}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Atlanta]