ent animator|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Nick Cross''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] independent animator. His works include ''The Waif of Persephone'', ''Yellow Cake'', ''Pig Farmer'', and ''Black Sunrise'',<ref name=\"pig\">{{cite journal|author=Ritika Bhandari|journal=Animation Reporter Magazine|title=Pig Farmer|issue=May 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"ASIFA\">{{citation|people=Danny Young, Michael Woodside|title=Nick Cross interview|publisher=ASIFA-Hollywood Animation Archive|date=March 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"king\">{{cite journal|title=King of Videos|journal=Ottawa Magazine|issue=October 2009}}</ref><ref>{{citation|work=Catsuka|publisher=NOLIFE|url=http://www.catsuka.com/player.php?id=catsuka_emission_30|title=Nick Cross|year=2011}}</ref> which he wrote, directed, animated and produced. He is friends with [[graphic novel]] artist [[Troy Little]]<ref name=\"fulle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fullecirclemagazine.com/2008/06/conversation-with-nick-cross.html|title=Conversation with Nick Cross|author=Jason Anders|work=Fulle Circle Magazine|date=2008|accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref> and they collaborated on the development of the animated series ''Angora Napkin''. He directed the pilot for the [[Nickelodeon]] series ''[[Pig Goat Banana Cricket]]'' created by graphic novel creator [[Dave Cooper]] and [[alternative comics]] creator [[Johnny Ryan]]. He was the art director for the [[Cartoon Network]] acclaimed mini-series ''[[Over the Garden Wall]]'' as well as the [[Cartoon Network Shorts Department|network's shorts development program]]. He is currently supervising producer on the upcoming Cartoon Network series ''Tig n' Seek''.\n\nHe is married to cartoonist [[Marlo Meekins]].\n\n==Black Sunrise==\n''Black Sunrise'' is a planned feature-film, produced and animated entirely by Nick Cross. Cross began the film before the rise in popularity of the internet, at which time he considered notions like [[the Illuminati]] and secret societies more mysterious and interesting to the general public than they are today. After completing 15 minutes of animation, time constraints prevented Cross from continuing his work on the film. Cross believes that the film, if completed, will not be received favorably because the topic of secret societies is overexposed, but he might still release segments of the film.<ref>{{cite|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LmiLxmAOJIk|title=Startoon Cartoon Podcast - Episode 19 - The One With Nick Cross Part 2|date=December 13, 2017|time=the start of the video and later from 20 minutes onward|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{BLP sources section|date=April 2016}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=100%\n|-style=\"background:#b0c4de; text-align:center;\"\n! width=50px| Year\n! width=300px | Title\n! Credit\n! Notes\n! width=30px | Ref.\n|-\n| 1997 || ''[[Rupert (TV series)|Rupert]]'' || layout artist || 13 episodes ||\n|-\n| 2001\u20132003 || ''[[Untalkative Bunny]]'' || storyboard artist ||  ||  \n|-\n| 2001 || ''The Red Scarf'' || producer, writer, animator, director ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/40332276|title=The Red Scarf|author=Nick Cross|date=April 13, 2012|accessdate=May 3, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2001\u20132002 || ''[[The Ripping Friends]]'' || model clean-up ||  || \n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Ren & Stimpy Adult Party Cartoon]]'' || art director, background designer, storyboard artist || || \n|- \n| \"align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\"|2006 || ''[[Tenacious D]]'' - \"Classico\" || background artist ||  || <ref name=\"fulle\" />\n|- \n| ''The Waif of Persephone'' || producer, writer, animator, director ||  || <ref name=\"ASIFA\" />\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Wayside (TV series)|Wayside]]'' || storyboard artist || 2 episodes || \n|-\n| 2008 || [[Danko Jones]] - \"King of Magazines\" || animator, co-director || Collaboration with [[Dave Cooper]] and Steve Stefanelli. || <ref name=\"king\" />\n|-\n| \"align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\"|2009 || ''Angora Napkin'' || co-creator, designer, animator, storyboard artist, background 